  "prompt": "How strategically important is Myanmar to Indonesia?",
  "response": "Myanmar is strategically important to Indonesia in several ways, though not as critically significant as some other regional relationships:\n\n1. Regional Geopolitics\n- Both are members of ASEAN\n- Share concerns about regional stability\n- Engage in regional diplomatic dialogues\n\n2. Security Considerations\n- Potential refugee and migration issues\n- Concerns about regional instability\n- Shared interest in managing cross-border challenges\n\n3. Economic Interactions\n- Limited but existing trade relationships\n- Potential for economic cooperation\n- Opportunities for investment and collaboration\n\n4. Diplomatic Engagement\n- Indonesia has occasionally played a mediation role in Myanmar's internal conflicts\n- Supports ASEAN's principles of non-interference and peaceful resolution\n\n5. Strategic Location\n- Myanmar's position between Southeast Asian countries is geopolitically relevant\n- Impacts regional connectivity and economic corridors\n\nWhile Myanmar is important, it's not among Indonesia's top-tier strategic priorities. Indonesia tends to focus more on relationships with larger economies and more immediate neighbors like China, Australia, and regional ASEAN states.\n\nThe strategic significance is moderate, with diplomatic and regional stability considerations being the primary areas of mutual interest.",
